      "name": "Aeon Stone Swarm",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png",
            "name": "Treasure and Rewards",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "aeon stones",
              "aonid": 3055,
              "game-obj": "Equipment",
              "name": "aeon stones",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Aeon Stones",
          "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
          "sidebar_type": "treasure_and_rewards",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Pathfinder #215: To Blot Out the Sun pg. 82",
                "aonid": 259,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Pathfinder #215: To Blot Out the Sun pg. 82",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Pathfinder #215: To Blot Out the Sun",
              "page": 82,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "When an aeon stone swarm is destroyed, most of the *aeon stones* composing its body shatter and explode, but a few remain whole. Adventurers willing to sift through mounds of sharp *aeon stone* shards are usually rewarded with a consumed aeon stone, a *preserving aeon stone*, or a *sprouting aeon stone*\u2014perhaps even a *nourishing aeon stone* or *smoothing aeon stone* for the particularly lucky!",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Pathfinder #215: To Blot Out the Sun pg. 82",
            "aonid": 259,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Pathfinder #215: To Blot Out the Sun pg. 82",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Pathfinder #215: To Blot Out the Sun",
          "page": 82,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Aeon stone swarms are constructs composed of hundreds of magical gems called *aeon stones* that orbit around a central point in a tumultuous, evershifting mass. Each swarm is imbued with intelligence and composed of a collection of *aeon stones*, which can arrange themselves in a variety of configurations to activate unique resonant powers. While most aeon stone swarms adopt similar configurations, it's possible to create swarms with experimental structures, resulting in different or additional resonant powers.   \n  \nMany aeon stone swarms are created to protect a particular location clandestinely, with the swarm using its subterfuge resonance to disguise itself as a mosaic of precious stones or a pile of gemstones lying in an open chest. Unfortunately for would-be thieves, nearly all the aeon stones composing an aeon stone swarm shatter when the swarm is destroyed.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "link": {
        "alt": "Pathfinder #215: To Blot Out the Sun pg. 82",
